Rock-Paper-Scissors Game 🎮

A simple Python implementation of the classic Rock–Paper–Scissors game.
You play against the computer, and the game keeps track of scores until you decide to stop.

📋 Features

Play Rock, Paper, Scissors against the computer.

Keeps track of your score, computer score, and ties.

Runs until you choose to quit.

Simple terminal-based game.

🛠 Requirements

Python 3.10+ (tested on Python 3.13)

No external libraries required (uses only Python's built-in random module).

▶️ How to Run

Save the code in a file called main.py (or any name you like).

Open a terminal and navigate to the folder where your file is saved.

Run the program:

python main.py


Follow the on-screen instructions to play.

🕹️ How to Play

Enter 1 for Rock, 2 for Paper, or 3 for Scissors.

The computer will randomly choose its move.

The winner of the round will be displayed.

Scores will be updated automatically.

You can continue playing by entering Y or quit by entering N.